Task 7: Device Security
This section covers hardware-based security features designed to protect the integrity of the device.
Core Isolation A virtualization-based security feature. Memory Integrity is a subset of this which prevents attacks from inserting malicious code into high-security processes.
Security Processor (TPM) The Trusted Platform Module (TPM) is a dedicated crypto-processor chip on the motherboard designed to secure hardware. It makes the machine tamper-resistant and stores cryptographic keys. It ensures that malicious software cannot tamper with the security functions of the machine.

